           &emsp; &emsp; If an example  ğ‘¥  has a low probability  $p(x) < \epsilon$ , then it is classified as an anomaly. To get predictions for each example (0/ False for normal and 1/True for anomaly), you can use <code>predictions = (p_val < epsilon)</code>
